All right!
The fifth chapter's all set now.
So let us have our meeting about the plot of the seventh chapter.
Okay.
What is with you guys?
Are you that worried about your second chapter getting 8th place?
Rather than worried...
If we look at Baked Cheese's rankings,
it is quite possible that our third chapter will fall into a double-digit ranking as well.
Double-digits...
Hey now, guys.
You need to have more confidence!
Even though Cheese is in 12th place, it is not getting canceled!
You guys are fine!
Are you completely sure?
Well, I cannot say that with 100 certainty, but as long as you do not fall to 18th or 19th place, I am 99 sure!
If you are not 100 sure, you are not completely sure!
There is no 100 in this world!
Do not keep making a fuss!
But you are...
But if four new titles get serialized,
then everything below 15th place is in danger...
What is it with you two?
TRAP will definitely be fine!
More importantly, let us have our meeting about the next chapter.
Good morning!
You, too.
I left the early results on your desk.
Ah, yes.
Thank you.
The third chapter is in 9th place!
See?
It only fell one ranking!
It looks like TRAP will continue, does not it?
Yeah!
It is great!
But Ashirogi Mutou and Niizuma are doing this while still in high school...
They are really something.
I think so, too.
Of course, Niizuma graduated this spring.
Oh, that is right.
9th place is great!
he says.
What do you think?
If you can change it, I think you should.
Our third chapter got 9th place.
Miura said it is okay, but...
With this story, it takes three chapters to resolve a case.
The next serialization meeting is in two days, and I do not think we will be canceled, but...
I do not know what will happen when the next results come in.
But if we do not have a certain amount of buildup in the story, it will not be good reading as a mystery.
Yeah.
And Miura said we should just keep going with what we are doing now.
We will be fine as long as our volumes sell.
That is still a ways off.
And I do not think it will sell well with the ranking it is got now.
I do not think so, either.
You should not just believe what Miura says.
I was a finalist for the Tezuka Award and Miura picked me up, but...
He said
This will be fine!
and I turned in three different manuscripts...
but none of them even got the monthly prize.
I do not want to say anything bad about someone who is willing to take on challenging projects,
but he does not have much experience and he is too optimistic.
So I am just trying to submit works that I think are good.
But it will be bad if I just change the storyboard without consulting him...
You are the one who is ultimately in charge of the plot.
I will draw whatever you feel is best.
With that, we have to show Miura the storyboard two days from now.
I have to pen-in the sixth chapter, so I do not have much time for major changes.
Yes?
Just a moment.
Sensei, Hiramaru is here.
Oh, it is Hiramaru!
Please tell him to wait.
I will be right there.
Click.
Niizuma!
Hide me please!
Are you being chased by bad people?
More like the police.
I respect all manga authors.
19 pages, week after week.
It is not human!
Are not you doing it, too?
I am at my limit already.
Working at a normal company was 100 times better.
It suits me more.
I was happy having weekends off.
My editor says you cannot do this kind of work unless you like it.
I like it, so it is fun for me.
That must be how it is.
I do not really like manga,
so it is hard to do it as a career.
If you want to quit, just talk to the chief editor.
I am sure he will cancel it for you.
Huh?
It can be stopped?
This is Yoshida from Yueisha.
It is Mr. Yoshida!
Hiramaru!
I know you are in there!
Come out quietly!
Whoa, he really is like the police.
How did he know I was here?!
I called him!
Y-You!
You are annoying!
When I look at you, I just get really pissed off!
We are betting our careers as manga authors on the serialization meeting two days from now!
So what the hell are you going on about here?
Do not screw with me!
S-Sorry!
What should I do?
All you have to do is draw manga.
Hiramaru's kind of pitiful, do not you think?
Not at all!
Even though we know it will not get canceled,
it sucks waiting for that phone call on the day of the serialization meeting.
Shut up and ink.
What is with that?
You are always telling me to talk more and liven things up.
Shut up.
Eh, already?
Is not it early this time?
Hi, this is Mashiro.
Oh, Mashiro?
TRAP is fine, like I told you.
Thank you.
Two new serializations have been decided on this time.
YES!
Finally, my time has come!
I did it!
This is great!
Both of you are serialized!
Double Congratulations!
Thank you, thank you!
I am finally serialized with Aoki... it is good to be alive.
But you two cannot work with me anymore...
I am kind of sad.
Do not be ridiculous.
We will be serialized in Jack together!
There is nothing better than that!
Take down CROW!
No, take down every other manga!
I will not lose to KIYOSHI or door.
Come at me, bro.
Yeah!
I will not lose, either!
Aoki and I!
I see... yes.
Both KIYOSHI Knights and hideout door at once, huh?
Awesome.
This is bad.
The Golden Future Cup.
In the last serialization meeting, those were the works we were competing against.
I am sure they reworked them and brought them back to the table.
And the ones that are ending are Takano's Chain Gold...
and Arai's Baked Cheese.
Eh?
Baked Cheese is canceled?
That was fast!
Even though Cheese is in 12th place, it is not getting canceled!
You guys are fine!
Saiko.
Um, Miura, can you hold on for a minute?
What is it, Shujin?
I am going to change chapter seven's storyboard right now!
Change, you say?
Our third chapter was at 9th place... at this rate, we are finished!
Our goal is for an anime production, right?
With our ranking right now, we cannot...
Th-That is right...
An anime, huh.
Well, with a Jack serialization, anyone would think about that.
I do not want to lose to KIYOSHI Knights or hideout door.
And of course, not to CROW or Otters 11 either!
Me either!
I do not want to lose!
Then let us redo the storyboard!
Miura, this is Takagi.
Oh, Takagi.
Sorry for keeping you waiting.
I know, really.
So what is up?
Have you finished chapter seven's storyboard?
Um, I have to ask your opinion about that.
Actually...
What?!
You want to change the storyboard?!
What are you talking about?
You said you would show it to me today!
You have to draw it according to our arrangement at the meeting!
No, I do not think things will go well like this.
Let us have another meeting!
Another one?!
Anyway, it is tough for me to talk here.
I will call you from my cell.
Jeez, what is he thinking?
What is wrong?
Ah, nothing.
Oh right, Aida.
TRAP was not brought up as a candidate for cancellation in today's meeting, was it?
Nope.
Not this time.
It might be in danger by the next meeting, though.
If it keeps falling, I do not know what will happen in two months.
That is...
It is your job to make sure it does not come up as a candidate for cancellation!
You would better discuss this throughly with the authors.
But... the direction TRAP is taking is not wrong, correct?
Yeah.
I think the classic mystery approach is good.
I know, right?!
If that does not work out, oh well.
Oh well...?
Oops, I have to call them.
Sorry I kept you waiting.
It is fine.
Can we continue this conversation tomorrow when I come to pick up the manuscript?
Tomorrow?
I would like to talk about it before then, but...
I understand.
Tomorrow, chapter six's manuscript will be finished and Mashiro will have time for a meeting.
Okay.
I will also bring the storyboard we already agreed on.
All right.
See you tomorrow.
Why are you sighing, Miura?
Well, it is about TRAP...
They want to change the storyboard all of a sudden.
Well, they did get a mediocre ranking.
Mediocre?
Do you really think so?
Getting 9th place on your third chapter is not that great.
I would support them on this.
There is no way those two would be satisfied with 9th place.
Obviously, they are going to aim higher!
Um, how exactly should I support them?
How should I know?
You are their editor.
Miura, you would be better off not supporting them.
TRAP is the kind of manga that will get more popular on it is own, slowly but surely.
T-That is right!
No, he should help them out.
A mystery will never be popular in Jack!
It should set up an interesting mystery and tricks, no matter how many chapters that takes.
If they do that, it will definitely get popular.
How about seeing how it goes if you resolve mysteries in one chapter?
No, if you do that, the tricks will be cheap.
You should build it up slowly over many chapters.
And I have been saying that kind of of mystery is not suited for Jack!
H-Hey everybody, stop saying different things!
I will get even more confused!
Anyways, with a double-digit ranking they will not be able to keep it going.
What is Miura doing?
He is worried about the direction TRAP should be taking.
That is bad, is not it?
The longer it runs, the more popular it will get.
But most manga get canceled before they reach that point.
If the editor's in this state, he is not going to get good results from his authors.
Heishi, go over there.
Yes, sir.
Hey, do not get full of yourself just because CROW's popular!
Yoshida, you should not go thinking that you are right all the time, either, just because Otters 11 got a good reception!
Hey, hey...
Hey, this is about the gap!
Wait, why am I trying to smooth things over here?
That has nothing to do with this!
That is enough, all of you.
Sorry, we just...
Have more confidence in yourself, Miura!
Y-Yes sir.
Listen, do not have that kind of attitude in front of the authors.
Yes, I am sorry.
Furthermore, Yoshida and Yuujirou should not butt in on other people's manga!
Come on, back to work.
Yeah.
Which is it?
I have until tomorrow to decide on my opinion as their editor.
Support them, huh?
Those two should be all right as long as they do not rush into a decision...
Well, we will be leaving now.
Have a good evening!
Good work today!
Hey, are not you guys going to call Fukuda to congratulate him?
We should do that to be polite, but I am not in the mood for it with all this worrying about chapter seven.
But they called you when you got serialized!
They might be busy with their new serialization, too.
Huh?
She is right.
The least we could do is make a short call.
Right, right.
Try it, but hang up if they are too busy.
Oh, thanks, Mashiro!
You did not have to call.
Yeah, if I failed this time, I was going to punch Yuujirou.
TRAP's been having a tough fight, yeah?
Are you okay?
A tough fight... it does seem that way after all.
Hello?
I am giving the phone to Nakai.
Oh, okay.
Hey Mashiro!
Thanks a lot!
Even though I am past 30, I will be in your care.
Uh, yeah.
Let us try our best together.
By the way, I am about to go meet up with Aoki now.
R-Right.
This moment has finally come.
We are going to change Jack.
Everyone who talked about that has become serialized!
Yes.
We are going to change Jack...
But as it is now, TRAP will...!
Ashirogi!
Eiji!
Detective TRAP is really interesting!
It is good to differentiate from Jack's normal stuff.
The stories that Takagi makes are really well done.
I am surprised!
Ah, thank you.
Eiji said your stories were well done.
Of course they are, right?
If Eiji says that from his 3rd place ranking, I cannot hear it as anything but sarcasm.
Hey, hey.
Anyways, how should I change the seventh chapter?
For it to be popular, I suppose I have put in some kind of battle...
It is good to differentiate from Jack's normal stuff.
What does that mean?
I just drew out an idea I had...
Okay.
What do you think?
Does it look like good material?
Hmm.
If we were to go in a Jack-like direction, it would be this, I guess.
I reread popular manga all night and came up with some new material.
I was planning on refining it a bit more for tonight's meeting.
And we have to think of a way to persuade Miura.
Well, I will figure something out.
Yeah, you are right.
It is as we discussed before... no, it is even better.
I think this is good.
I have prepared some ideas on how to change it
No need for that.
You have not even seen them!
We want to improve our ranking!
Do not be so presumptuous.
Your final ranking was also 9th.
That is good enough.
If you make a bad move, you will fail.
B-But...
Instead of aiming higher, right now you should be aiming to keep 9th place.
What is with that?!
That is not right!
Should not we always be trying to aim higher?!
TRAP is not that kind of manga!
Miura...
Right now, you need to have patience.
You have to let the mystery get firmly established.
I do not think that is true.
I feel our ranking will drop at this rate
It is okay for it to drop a bit!
Do not freak out!
I have one suggestion.
What is it?
Will you stop paying attention to survey results?
This is only my second year on the job,
but I have seen so many new guys fail because they worried too much about the results.
Originally, the ranking was not something we told authors.
But once they learned about the rankings, they would naturally want to hear the results.
O-Of course!
It worries us, and it is normal to refer to your past results going forward
I thought that up until yesterday.
But it is tough to have the rankings thrown in your face.
That is why you are talking about changing the plot over a 9th place ranking.
He is right... it may be better to do it without knowing the survey results.
Miura!
You said chapter seven is fine as is, but does that mean you think it will be popular?
I do not think so.
Do not screw with us!
Then I should change it!
I do not think it will be popular,
but I do not think it will drop much either.
If you change the story now, you destroy yourselves.
You will just hasten your cancellation.
You are saying that right now we are just staving off cancellation by the skin of our teeth!
That is true in a way.
Once you are serialized, you just have to keep it going one chapter at a time.
That is why this plot is fine.
Just add one chapter at a time the way you are doing now!
That is the best thing for this manga and for you!
Takahama said that he seems like a guy who cannot do anything,
but he is looking at TRAP more calmly than we are.
But manga is a gamble!
We have to put something on the line and aim for the top!
It is better to fail doing that than to do nothing at all!
No, that is wrong.
We need to go forward like this.
Even if it ends like this!
If it ends?
What are you saying?!
Saiko, you say something too!
Manga is a gamble.
Hey, Saiko!
Are you listening?
Will we win?
Or not?
Our first chapter was 3rd place.
Second was 8th.
Third was 9th.
Is it a winner or a loser?
Detective TRAP is really interesting!
It is good to differentiate from Jack's normal stuff.
I think Miura is right.
And suddenly, you are changing your mind too?!
Being a manga author is a gamble, but after you are serialized, maybe it is not.
Well, even if it is, what Shujin's doing is... desperate.
Whether it is a gamble or not, if we are desperate, we lose.
Saiko, I do not get what you are saying!
The stories you make are good!
Yeah, they are good!
Last night I read chapters one through six over and over again.
They are still really good!
Eiji said yesterday that it is good to differentiate from Jack's normal stuff.
That was praise, after all!
It is fine for a genuine mystery manga to be different from Jack's normal stuff!
In other magazines, this type of story is successful with readers.
We just need to let them know...
that there is a genuine mystery manga in Jack!
We have to pull the people who like that type of manga in!
Saiko...
If we are going to gamble on TRAP, I would rather continue with our style till the end and gather fans.
Your stories can do that!
I get it.
I will try my hardest with our current style.
Hello, hello.
It is Mecha.
Mecha CROW!
Oh, Ashirogi?
What is up?
I wanted to thank you.
Thank me?
Yes.
Actually, we were confused on which direction to take TRAP from now on.
What were you confused about?
It is good as is.
Yeah.
It is good.
Your words saved us!
I see.
Hiramaru, you said the same thing last week, It will be okay.
It looks like you persuaded them to take TRAP in the direction of a genuine mystery.
All right, I am coming now.
Yeah.
But really, it was Mashiro who said what I wanted to say.
Well, at any rate, everything worked out.
Yeah!
I thought he would say that they decided to take the easy road and turn it into a battle manga, but..
they have both grown.
But it will certainly be dangerous from now on.
I hope TRAP gets popular!
But it may not be suited for Jack.
You think so?
I mean, I want it to continue, too.
Comedy and News.
I think it is good!
